jeremyText="Oh, this is interesting. Remember the 'Wall Cancer' robot in Gate 4? It was the crab on the wall that shot two bouncing energy balls. This thing fires 12 of those, which can make things pretty spammy. It also has the ability to reverse its gravity and cling to the ceiling. Another thing to note is it will speed up the time it takes to fire its next shot when it is continually taking damage." chaoText="Spider Drones are love! Spider Drones are life! ...#What? I thought it was funny." devText="I had nearly all of the enemy AI for the end game prepped well in advance, which I typically didn't do for most of the different areas in the game. Most of the AI was made just before drawing out the levels. In some cases, the levels were made first, and the enemies were tailored for those environments afterwards."
